{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"690d8c5f-c0e3-41e3-b478-4d4c6692ef88","content":"Here's a quick overview by framework:\n\n### .NET (`dotnet new webapi`)\nAuth options via `--auth`:\n- **None** (default)\n- **IndividualB2C** – Azure AD B2C\n- **SingleOrg** – Azure AD (single tenant)\n- **MultiOrg** – Azure AD (multi-tenant)\n- **Windows** – Windows/NTLM/Kerberos\n\n### Node.js / Express\nNo built-in auth templates — typically add:\n- **Passport.js** (local, OAuth, JWT, etc.)\n- **express-jwt** / **jsonwebtoken**\n- **OAuth2 / OpenID Connect** providers\n\n### Python / FastAPI / Django\n- **FastAPI**: built-in OAuth2 + JWT support\n- **Django REST Framework**: session, token, OAuth2 via `django-oauth-toolkit`\n\n### Java / Spring Boot\n`spring-boot-starter-security` with:\n- **Basic / Form auth**\n- **OAuth2 / OpenID Connect**\n- **JWT**\n\nFor .NET specifically, you can explore all options with:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --help\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold a project in a specific framework?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7c699c9a-e95a-4697-988b-c5486cb96728","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the main frameworks and their auth options.","outputTokens":353,"requestId":"0404:1B1922:A78B48:D0D010:6A0128BE"},"id":"88d2542b-2583-4ae9-8ea6-614901d65262","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:54:31.122Z","parentId":"bead1f93-30af-4da0-83cf-e66da550827c"}
